 of the earliest families on Martha's Vineyard. — The surname <i>Bassett</i> of French origin (see 2 above) is listed in the register of Huguenot ancestors recognized by the Huguenot Society of America."],"variants":[{"name":"Bessette","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Marcel, Armand, Adrien, Normand, Alphonse, Lucien, Cecile, Herve, Jacques, Laurent, Aime.","French: topographic name designating a small wood of birches, from Occitan <i>bès</i> ‘birch tree’ (see   Besse  ), or a habitational name from (La) Bessette, the name of several places in the southern part of France.","Alternatively, an altered form of French <b>Besset</b>: topographic name, a cognate of 1 above. Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]}]},{"name":"Anselme","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from ‘divinity’ + ‘helmet’. St Anselm of Piedmont was Archbishop of Canterbury in the late 11th and early 12th centuries.  See  <b>Anselm</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":18,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":43,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":56,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":65,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":110,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Anselme Bassett was born about 1272, in Uley, Gloucestershire, England. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Margaret De Berkeley. He died in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1272–":"umbes 1272–Surnud","1274–1320":"1274–1320","–Female":"Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1272–Male":"1272–Surnud","about 1272":"umbes 1272","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1272":"1272","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Uley, Gloucestershire, England":"Uley, Gloucestershire, England","Kingsgrove, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1272–":"noin 1272–Kuollut","1274–1320":"1274–1320","–Female":"Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1272–Male":"1272–Kuollut","about 1272":"noin 1272","1274":"1274","1382":"1382","1272":"1272","1290":"1290","1305":"1305","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","about 1300":"noin 1300","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Uley, Gloucestershire, England":"Uley, Gloucestershire